As a business hotel, it's got some very nice features: 2 minutes from the airport, decent internet bandwidth, a nice business center with 4 HP towers and a laser printer, quick dry-cleaning, in-house coin laundry, quick in-and-out parking, and very close to restaurants.	Good service by the front desk: when I had a problem with the wifi internet, they brought me a regular wired modem.	The Business Center with free internet and printing was a nice surprise, and there was also wireless in the room.	We got a ground floor room which had TV with cable(BBC World News was nice for us Brits), huge bed, free WI FI, coffee maker but no fridge or microwave.